The use and legalisation of cannabis is rising around the world. About 147 million people, or 2.5% of the world population, consume cannabis. It is possible to consume too much cannabis, causing dizziness and nausea, commonly referred to as "greening out". Until recently, there were no recorded instances of anyone dying from using marijuana. You would need to consume 680kg of weed in 15 minutes for it to kill you. Money Monitor: Pot edibles may drive up life insurance premiums Cannabis edibles will soon be legal in Canada but because insurance companies treat these new pot products the same as smoking a joint, your life insurance premiums may take a hit as a result. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by
